Source: python-btrfs
Section: libs
Priority: extra
Maintainer: Hans van Kranenburg <hans.van.kranenburg@mendix.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 9),
               dh-python,
               python-all,
               python-setuptools,
               python3-all,
               python3-setuptools,
Standards-Version: 3.9.4

Package: python-btrfs
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${python:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Python module to inspect btrfs filesystems.
 The primary goal of this module is to be able to inspect the internals of an
 existing filesystem for educational purposes.
 .
 The python module acts as a wrapper around the low level kernel calls and
 btrfs data structures, presenting them as python objects with interesting
 attributes and references to other objects.
 .
 This package installs the library for Python 2.

Package: python3-btrfs
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${python3:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Python module to inspect btrfs filesystems. (Python 3)
 The primary goal of this module is to be able to inspect the internals of an
 existing filesystem for educational purposes.
 .
 The python module acts as a wrapper around the low level kernel calls and
 btrfs data structures, presenting them as python objects with interesting
 attributes and references to other objects.
 .
 This package installs the library for Python 3.

Package: munin-plugins-btrfs
Architecture: all
Depends: munin-node, python-btrfs
Priority: extra
Section: net
Description: Munin plugin to graph space usage of Btrfs filesystems.

Package: nagios-plugins-btrfs
Architecture: all
Depends: python-btrfs
Priority: extra
Section: net
Description: Nagios plugin to check space usage of Btrfs filesystems.
